            <title>[SPARK-16335] Structured streaming should fail if source directory does not exist</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-16335</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;In structured streaming, Spark does not report errors when the specified directory does not exist. This is a behavior different from the batch mode. This patch changes the behavior to fail if the directory does not exist (when the path is not a glob pattern).&lt;/p&gt;

